Victorian Football Association

Season 1887

 

Season Notes

The premiership was decided by the Proportional Points system only from the 1888 season onwards (VFA Meeting 7 October 1887).

For the 1887 season the premiership was awarded to the team with the least losses.

Following an appeal by Geelong, the Association decided the Ballarat Imperial vs Geelong match played on 2 July 1887 should count towards the premiership (VFA Meeting 12 August 1887).

Were this match not to count, and subsequent results remain as they occurred, a play-off for the premiership between Carlton and Geelong would have been required.

 

It was decided that according to the rules, no matches played on Jubilee Day should count in the reckoning for the premiership of the clubs under the Association (VFA Meeting 12 August 1887)

Length of games: June/July 50 min per half (25 minute quarters), other months 60 minutes (30 minute quarters).

 

Ballarat clubs

All games involving the Ballarat clubs, including those between themselves are listed here.

Notes:

- Teams ranked by least losses.

- Proportional Points system used from 1888 season included as an indication only.

- The percentage column (%) of 'Goals For' divided by 'Goals Against' is included as an indication only.

- Footscray ranked below other teams due to the low number of games played.

- The Ballarat clubs are listed in italics below the other clubs due to the low number of games played.

- Minimum of 18 games required to qualify for the Premiership from 1888 onwards, did not apply to 1887 season.

- Behinds were recorded but did not count towards the final score or in determining the result of matches.
